title: Military Points of Interest, North Korea Uncovered
name: Military Points of Interest, North Korea Uncovered
description:
http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/dprk/mayangdo.htm 
This is a kml file for Military points of interest from North Korea Uncovered. 

This Google Earth project offers an extensive mapping of North Korea's economic, cultural, political, and military infrastructures. Through the topic menu, users of this program have easy access to geographical information on North Korea's agriculture projects, aviation facilities, communications, hospitals, hotels, energy infrastructure, financial services, leisure destinations, manufacturing facilities, markets, mines, religious locations, restaurants, schools, and transportation infrastructure. In addition to locations of economic interest, this map also displays anti-aircraft locations, the Demilitarized Zone (DMZ) and Northern Line Limit Line (NLL), incarceration facilities, political monuments, political residencies, military bases, and nuclear facilities.

properties.name: 2 Chongju PC
properties.description: Chongju PC This is a PC becasue it doesn't have any torpedoes or missiles on it that I can see. If they were PTG they would have 4 CSS-N-1 launchers like the Soju PTG and the Osa I PGT. In between the two Chongju PC is a "skinnier" Shanghai II PC.

properties.name: 2 Soju PTG
properties.description: Soju PTG The Soju PTG looks very similar to the Osa I PTG that is also found in North Korea. The Soju PTG is slightly longer than the OSA I PTG.

properties.name: 5 chongjin PB
properties.description: Chongjin PB The easiest way to tell these apart from all the other PT and PB that use the same hull is that the Chongjin PB uses a massive 85mm tank turret. Look at the bow. The first "bump" is the 85mm gun. The second "bump" is the wheelhouse. Behind that there are two much smaller gun positions that are staggered. one it so the port, and the one at the bow is toward the starbord.

properties.description:
Joint Security Area (Panmunjom). This is the site where two US Officers and four Korean soldiers were killed by north korean soldiers while attempting to trim the branches of a tree that obstructed the view of this border crossing.

properties.name: High Bay Building
properties.description: The high bay processing building measures 10 by 20 meters and is probably used for vertical integration and dynamic testing of the rocket stages. The access road has a ten-meter radius, wide enough to support rocket and missile stages and their transporters.

properties.description: Komar PTG or Sohung PTG These two Missle Craft look so much alike it is pretty much impossible to tell them appart at the quality of imagery that google provides us.

properties.name: P-6 PT
properties.description: P-6 PT or Sinnam PT Both PTs are pretty much the same vessel so it's hard to tell them apart. The Sinnam PT has added deck rails and the P-6 PT does not. Look for more information on PT boats in general here. Picture is not of an actual P-6 PT but a similar vessel.
